ants."},{"role":"Trader / Merchant","location":"Westhampton, Hampshire County, Massachusetts","notes":"Per EH 1909 #529: 'He was a physician and also a trader at West Hampton, Mass.' — supplementing physician income with a trading operation, common pattern for rural New England doctors of the period."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Lived to ninety-four as Westhampton physician","body":"Born Northampton MA 1766; died Westhampton MA February 27, 1861 at age ninety-four — extraordinary longevity spanning the early Republic through the Civil War's outbreak. Practiced medicine in Westhampton MA and also operated as a trader; both occupations supported a large family of seven children with first wife Anna Thompson before her 1810 death."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Lost wife at forty-two, remarried after two years","body":"First wife Anna Thompson died Westhampton April 2, 1810 at age forty-two — leaving him with seven children ranging from twenty-four-year-old Henry down to eight-year-old Edward. William remarried 1812 to Rhoda Phelps, widow of Ensign Hartland of Hartland Connecticut. No documented children from the second marriage; Rhoda predeceased William by fourteen years."}],"former_ids":[],"slug":"william-hooker-1766"},"I01155":{"id":"I01155","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Anna","last_name":"Hooker","maiden_name":"Thompson","married_names":["Hooker"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Anna Thompson Hooker"},"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1768,"month":2,"day":25,"county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1810,"month":4,"day":2,"city":"Westhampton","county":"Hampshire","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"residence":{"city":"Westhampton","county":"Hampshire","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM544"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false